  "url": "https://www.lankadeepa.lk/news/\u2018\u2018\u0db8\u0dc4-\u0dbd\u0dda\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca-\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dda-\u0db8\u0dc4\u0dcf-\u0db6\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca\u2018\u2018/101-616524",
  "time_ut": 1657960076,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2018\u2018\u0db8\u0dc4 \u0dbd\u0dda\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db8\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0db6\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"The General Secretary told a big lie\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "We tell the leaders clearly who is the president to sit at a table and decide? Who is the prime minister? that Otherwise, don't go to the polls and waste crores and put the people under more pressure, said Kalutara District Member of Parliament Mr. Lalith Ellawala.",
        "Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna Secretary Sagara Kariyawasam says that the party has decided to vote for Ranil Wickramasinghe. No such decision was taken.",
        "We are the people who made the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna. And most of us were of the opinion that we should tell the candidates who have presented themselves to come forward and tell us their policies. After that, let's decide who will vote for who will be the president",
        "Sagara Kariyawasam is doing what he did then and is still doing today, he clearly tells the secretary not to give such naive and stupid decisions to the people as the opinion of the party.",
        "If you have a personal opinion, explain it. Do not give the opinion of the party, if that happens we as a party will have to take a decision about the secretary. This is a big lie.",
        "Even today, when the country has fallen so much, the secretary is clearly told not to do such olamotte work.",
        "As a party, all the members together take a decision against the secretary. All the leaders need to understand the situation the country is in today",
        "President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa who got 69 lakh votes was driven out by the people themselves. This is something that all leaders should understand.",
        "These people came to Colombo not because the Janata Vimukthi Peramuna said it, nor because the vanguards said it. People are under a lot of pressure. Unable to bear that oppression, the people stormed the presidential palace in hundreds of thousands on that day.",
        "We need to say especially to the current leaders that people will not come back to Colombo."
      ],
